            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>CPA (cost per acquisition) is often used at the campaign or channel level and can measure any conversion event (lead, signup, purchase). CAC (customer acquisition cost) is a company-wide metric measuring the total cost to acquire a paying customer, including all marketing, sales, and overhead.</p></div></div>
          </div>
